1. e4 c6 { Rather than play a third French, I chose to mix it up with the Caro Kann, an opening I like (but don't have much practice in). } 2. c4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. cxd5 Nf6 5. Qa4+ { Already here I was out of my book. I decided that I would just develop normally and try to ignore the weak doubled pawn. } 5... Nbd7 6. Nc3 g6 7. Bc4 Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. d3 Nb6 (9... a6! 10. O-O (10. Qa3 b6 11. O-O Bb7 12. Re1 (12. Be3 b5 13. Bb3 Nb6 14. Bxb6 Qxb6 15. Qxe7 a5 16. Qe3 Qxe3 17. fxe3 a4 18. Bd1 Nxd5 { [%csl Ge3] } 19. Nxd5 Bxd5) 12... Re8 13. Ng5 { [%cal Gg5e4] } 13... Rc8 14. d6 e6 { [%cal Gc1f4,Gf4d6] }) 10... b5! 11. Bxb5 Nb6 { My opponent told me that this is a trap white can fall into. If I had known anything about this position, I definitely would have gone for 9...a6. } { [%csl Ga4,Gb5][%cal Gb6a8] }) 10. Qb3 Bg4 11. Ne5 Bf5 12. O-O Qc7?! (12... Nfxd5 { The move I originally planned to play. I thought it failed due to: } 13. Nxf7 Rxf7 14. Nxd5 { But here I missed Nxc4 which secures a roughly even position. }) 13. Re1 { I could already tell I was much worse here. I had had a long tournament, and so was fine with just ending the game quickly. A more tenacious try is: } 13... Ng4?? (13... Nxc4 14. dxc4 Ne4 15. Nxe4 Qxe5 16. f3 { But this is still shaky at best for black. }) 14. Nxg4 Bxg4 { [%csl Gg5] } 15. h3 Bf5 16. Nb5 Qd8 17. Be3 (17. Bg5 Bf6 18. Bxf6 exf6 $16) 17... h6 18. Nxa7 Nxc4 19. dxc4 Qd7 { I knew I was lost, but I figured I would play for at least 25 moves just to see if there was any way to make it messy. } 20. Bc5 Rfe8 21. Nb5 Rac8 22. Bd4 e5 23. Bb6 (23. dxe6?! Bxe6 24. Bxg7 Bxc4 25. Rxe8+ Qxe8 { The line I was hoping for. }) 23... Bf8 24. Rac1 Rc5 25. Bxc5 Bxc5 26. Qc3 Qe7 27. d6 Qg5 28. a3 { No sacrifices against the white king do anything. And with b4 coming (kicking my best bishop away from the attack), I decided to resign, content with my 50% score in my first tournament. } { [%cal Ge5e4] } (28. Rxe5?? Rxe5 29. Qxe5 Qxc1+ $19 { This was the last attempt I had, but my opponent obviously kept a solid position. }) 1-0


